                <head>219. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>During meetings in Washington November 19-21, 1969, Japanese Prime Minister
                        <persName corresp="#p_SE3">Sato</persName> and President <persName
                        corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> discussed a wide range of matters of
                    mutual concern, including bilateral trade and textiles. See <ref
                        target="frus1969-76v03#d30">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1969–1976, volume III, Document
                        30</ref>. Additional documentation on the Summit is scheduled for
                    publication in a forthcoming volume of <hi rend="italic">Foreign
                    Relations</hi>.</p>
            </div>
